 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.3.2","title":"robot-redesign/adapters: build work and coordination normalization adapter","description":"Normalize work and coordination signals such as beads/bv state, Agent Mail unread/backlog state, file conflicts, reservation conflicts, and handoff context into shared projection sections. This task exists because operator pain often comes from coordination state rather than from tmux state alone.","design":"The adapter should produce stable work and coordination sections that can answer questions like: what is ready, what is blocked, who has unread mail, where are reservation conflicts, what is the current handoff summary, and which coordination problems deserve attention.\n\nThe implementation should hide the peculiarities of each source tool so later surfaces can reason about coordination with one vocabulary.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when work and coordination sections can be populated from beads/bv, Agent Mail, tracker/conflict data, and handoff data without leaking each tool's bespoke output model upward.","notes":"This adapter is where the redesign becomes more agent-intuitive than today's scattered bridge commands.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":240,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:26.022106327Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:51.053564627Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["adapters","coordination","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:51.052836664Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:26.022106327Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.3.3","title":"robot-redesign/adapters: build system, quota, alert, and health normalization adapter","description":"Normalize non-tmux operational signals such as quota pressure, health checks, alerts, and system-level warnings into shared projection sections. This task exists because operator decisions require a coherent operational picture, not just pane state plus occasional bespoke warnings.","design":"The adapter should define how health summaries, rate-limit signals, quota warnings, crash/restart state, and system degradation are represented in stable sections and reason codes.\n\nIt should also ensure those signals can later promote into incidents instead of remaining forever as disconnected ephemeral warnings.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when global operational signals can be surfaced in the projection model with stable section names and reason-code-friendly data.","notes":"If a future consumer has to parse free-form alert text to understand quota or health state, this adapter task has failed.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:26.913850553Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:51.517121862Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["adapters","health","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:51.516426791Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:26.913850553Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.3.4","title":"robot-redesign/adapters: compute source_health, freshness, and degraded feature state","description":"Compute source_health and degraded-feature information from all major adapters so every later surface can explain what is fresh, stale, partial, or unavailable. This task exists because freshness semantics must be produced systematically, not improvised by each renderer.","design":"The implementation should take adapter outputs plus failure states and emit section-level freshness and degradation metadata according to the contract defined earlier. It should decide how partial refreshes are represented, how source outages affect downstream sections, and how degraded features are advertised without drowning the response in noise.\n\nThis task is the bridge between adapter mechanics and trustworthy operator-facing semantics.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when runtime projections carry deterministic source_health and degraded feature state for all major sections and when later surfaces can reuse that data verbatim.","notes":"A surface should not have to decide on its own whether data are fresh or degraded. That decision belongs here.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":150,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:27.816413037Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:51.988828208Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["adapters","freshness","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:51.988102289Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:27.816413037Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:36.827359755Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:37.667671007Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:38.071801088Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","title":"robot-redesign/adapters: implement redaction, safe previews, and disclosure metadata across normalized sources","description":"Implement the source-side and projection-side redaction path that lets ntm expose richer robot data without leaking secrets or sensitive text into live surfaces, durable projections, or replay artifacts.","design":"The implementation should introduce a disciplined disclosure-control layer in the normalization pipeline. It should decide where text and structured payloads are classified and sanitized before persistence or projection, how pane tails, mail snippets, diagnostic evidence, actuation arguments or outcomes, and replay snapshots produce safe previews instead of raw sensitive blobs, and how disclosure metadata such as redaction markers, rule versions, hashed evidence handles, and counts of hidden material are carried into the shared model. It should also decide whether and how ntm keeps a lightweight redaction audit trail in SQLite so diagnostics, docs, and tests can verify that sensitive material was transformed rather than silently dropped. This work should preserve operator usefulness: evidence should remain explainable and correlatable even when the raw content is hidden.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when normalized robot-visible source data can flow through ntm with deterministic redaction or disclosure-control behavior, safe previews where appropriate, explicit machine-readable markers for hidden or transformed content, and enough auditability that replay, diagnostics, and validation can prove the system did the safe thing rather than merely omitting data.","notes":"If secrets can still slip from tmux output, mail content, diagnostic evidence, or replay artifacts into robot surfaces without an explicit and testable disclosure decision, this task is incomplete.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-22T01:34:08.686306044Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T01:34:35.227170128Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["adapters","robot-redesign","sensitivity"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:34:08.686306044Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.4","title":"robot-redesign/attention: persistent journal, replay, and cursor semantics","description":"Persist the attention journal and related output/activity watermarks so ntm's operator loop survives process restarts and exposes replay-safe, cursor-safe deltas across CLI and server transports. This epic exists because the attention loop is already the best direction in ntm, but it still needs durable mechanics to become the true center of the robot interface.","design":"The intended outcome is a durable event stream with stable cursor semantics, bounded retention, deterministic replay, explicit resync behavior, and enough persisted output/activity context to compute deltas even after ntm restarts.\n\nThis epic also owns transport parity: replay semantics should not diverge between CLI JSON, REST, SSE, and WebSocket consumers.","acceptance_criteria":"This epic is complete when events, digest, and attention can operate over durable journal state instead of volatile in-memory-only assumptions.","notes":"The attention feed should become more central, not more magical. It remains a sensing and triage surface, not a hidden planner.","status":"open","priority":4,"issue_type":"epic","estimated_minutes":300,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:07.747504415Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:20.457426809Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["attention","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:07.747504415Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":316,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Future self: the operator loop is the product. Treat any cursor ambiguity, replay drift, or restart breakage as a first-order defect.","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:08Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.4.1","title":"robot-redesign/attention: implement SQLite-backed attention event store and cursor model","description":"Implement the durable event store and cursor model that back ntm's replay-safe attention loop. This task exists because a central product promise of the redesign is that attention, events, and digest survive process restarts and expose stable delta semantics.","design":"The design should define event identity, cursor generation, retention windows, replay ordering, and how durable journal state relates to runtime projections and source health. The implementation should make cursor expiration and resync explicit instead of leaving them as accidental behavior.\n\nThis task should also preserve the existing attention-feed intent while upgrading its durability and transport neutrality.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when ntm can append and replay durable attention events from SQLite with stable ordering and explicit cursor semantics that later digest/attention/transport tasks can rely on.","notes":"Treat the cursor model as contract-critical. If it is vague, every delta consumer becomes brittle.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":240,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:28.716724326Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:53.419658726Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["attention","events","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:52.457652326Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:52.932305610Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:53.418895657Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:28.716724326Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":325,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.1","author":"ubuntu","text":"Future self: this task is where the current good attention-feed direction becomes restart-safe infrastructure instead of a clever in-memory convenience.","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:29Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.4.2","title":"robot-redesign/attention: publish durable events from adapters and monitors","description":"Emit durable attention events from the normalized adapters and monitoring logic instead of synthesizing them only in ad hoc surface code. This task exists because the durable journal only matters if source changes and operator-significant events are published consistently at the right seam.","design":"The publication model should define which normalized changes become events, which categories and reason codes they carry, how duplicate/noisy events are suppressed, and which events remain background versus action-required.\n\nThis is where we make event production systematic rather than letting each renderer invent its own idea of what changed.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when major normalized sources can publish durable attention events with stable categories, reason codes, and actionability semantics into the SQLite journal.","notes":"If event meaning still depends on where you read it from, this task is incomplete.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:29.989067017Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:57.716089849Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["attention","publish","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:56.756502539Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:57.236294556Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:57.715435965Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:29.989067017Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:38.473709208Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
